Sentencas: The high sintering temperature of Yttrium doped barium zirconate (BZY), the most promising high temperature proton conductor (HTPC) for Intermediate Temperature (400-750 degrees C) Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (IT-SOFCs), has been reduced by using ZnO as a sintering aid.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of spin coated dense BaZr0.80Y0.16Zn0.04O3-δ membranes

Sentencas: Obtaining a dense electrolyte at a reduced temperature allows conventional fuel cell preparation methods.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of spin coated dense BaZr0.80Y0.16Zn0.04O3-δ membranes

Sentencas: A reproducible spin coating method to fabricate highly performing anode supported button cells with dense micrometric BZYZn electrolyte layers has been developed.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of spin coated dense BaZr0.80Y0.16Zn0.04O3-δ membranes

Sentencas: The electrochemical characterization of button cells at 600 degrees C shows promising performance, higher than that of comparable fuel cells from literature.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of spin coated dense BaZr0.80Y0.16Zn0.04O3-δ membranes
